   <mods:abstract>While the United States are grateful for Spain's offer to pay off the
            outstanding bills of exchange at the end of a two year period, it is likely that there
            will be many holders who will bring suit rather than wait for the two year period to
            end. Giving the United States frigates will be of little assistance in sustaining her
            public credit; also frigates can be built more cheaply in America. The proposal that
            United States ships aid in preying on British trade to the East Indies is flattering,
            but the uncertain state of the war in America precludes any permanent support in this
            regard.</mods:abstract>
